@impowski the `relay.Node.Field` is meant to implement a field that you fetch by using the relay id. If you would like to be able to find a user using other criteria you will have to implement your own field resolver. For example:

```python
class Query(graphene.ObjectType):
    user = graphene.Field(UserType, username=graphene.String(required=True))
    all_users = DjangoFilterConnectionField(UserType)

	def resolve_user(root, info, username):
		return UserModel.objects.get(username=username)
```

