@alanfranz I think you bring up a lot of good points - it really shouldn't be the case that the packaged certbot install breaks other packages on your Ubuntu version, especially if the versions of packages you have are above what certbot requires.
@oerdnj It seems like the versions of dependencies you're shipping correspond mostly to whatever is in Ubuntu trunk. While this makes things simple, it does seems like it has high potential for causing issues for users who aren't on the latest Ubuntu release. I understand that it's significant work to ship multiple sets of libraries, so I think my recommendation would be to ship a set of libraries that correspond with our minimum requirements for certbot. That way old versions of Ubuntu would get newer packages when they need it, but newer versions could safely ignore your packages.

As for people who are experiencing breakage, I would recommend uninstalling the PPA version of certbot and re-installing it using the certbot-auto script so that all packages are kept in a virtual environment
